# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BRIAN NYAMBEGO — CONTENT MANAGEMENT SYSTEM (Notion)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
# The site works WITHOUT these — it shows fallback content.
# Add them when you're ready for live Notion content.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1. Get your Notion Integration Token:
#    Go to: https://www.notion.so/my-integrations
#    Create a new integration, copy the "Internal Integration Token"
NOTION_TOKEN=secret_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# 2. Create databases in Notion, then share each with your integration.
#    Copy the database ID from the URL: notion.so/{workspace}/{DATABASE_ID}?v=...

# Cohorts database — Brian's active and upcoming cohorts
NOTION_COHORTS_DB=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Books database — all published titles
NOTION_BOOKS_DB=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Webinars database
NOTION_WEBINARS_DB=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Events / Speaking database
NOTION_EVENTS_DB=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Blog posts database
NOTION_BLOG_DB=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Testimonials database
NOTION_TESTIMONIALS_DB=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
